            "title": "Simply Good Foods Gears Up For Q2 Print; Here Are The Recent Forecast Changes From Wall Street's Most Accurate Analysts",
            "id": "78efb548-26e7-4379-a2ae-ed4267cde5c6",
            "description": "Before the trading session begins on Thursday, April 9, The Simply Good Foods Company (NASDAQ: SFPL) will report its second quarter earnings. Analysts are predicting a quarterly profit of 40 cents per share, a decrease from the 46 cents per share reported in the same period last year. The consensus among analysts for the company's quarterly revenue stands at $344.08 million, a decline from the $359.65 million revenue reported last year. Joe Scalzo took over as the president and CEO on Jan. 20, succeeding Geoff Tanner. The company's stock closed at $14.22 on Monday, showing a 0.4% increase. For more details, analyst ratings can be found on the Analyst Stock Ratings page.",
